                            <comment id="17585652" author="jbull" created="Sat, 27 Aug 2022 03:13:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve also encountered this. This is especially problematic when the stream is bursty and the last batch of messages encounters a RetriableException. In such a case, the offsets will never be committed resulting in sustained lag.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposed fix in &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/12566/commits/109ad70e20206cc82ebb155776b42e547cdd243d&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/kafka/pull/12566/commits/109ad70e20206cc82ebb155776b42e547cdd243d&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
